The US Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA) requires that you enter into a contract to ensure safeguarding of protected health information (PHI).
If you or your company is a covered entity as defined by HIPAA, turn on this setting to accept the IBM Business Associate Agreement (BAA) and enable this account to run sensitive workloads regulated under HIPAA.

Virtual routing and forwarding: Off
Virtual routing and forwarding (VRF) isolates the IP routing for services in your account to a separate routing table. Learn more.
Important: Enabling VRF permanently alters networking for your account and cannot be undone.
To turn on VRF for this account, open a support case. This option applies only to billable accounts.
Service endpoints: Off
IBM Cloud service endpoints enable you to connect to select services over the IBM Cloud private network instead of the public network. Connecting directly to service endpoints does not require internet access, providing increased security. Learn more.
Virtual routing and forwarding must be enabled before you can turn on service endpoints.
